\begin_layout Subsection
Immediate happiness and immediate environment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this second strand of research we design, implement, and collect and
 analyse panel data from an ESM study using participants' own smartphones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We develop a native software application (app) named 
\emph on
Mappiness
\emph default
 for the Apple iPhone.
 The app is distributed via the App Store, a central software repository
 accessible to all device users.
 Participants are recruited opportunistically, assisted by coverage in tradition
al and social media.
 Prospective participants download the app at no charge, indicate their
 informed consent to take part, and provide some basic demographic information.
 They are then signalled at random moments and asked to report on their
 mood on a continuous sliding scale.
 They are also asked whom they are with, where they are, and what they are
 doing.
 While they answer, their precise location is determined by GPS.
 All data are then transmitted wirelessly to our server.
 Participants receive simple feedback, charting their happiness in different
 contexts, and can take part for as long or short a period as they wish.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
